parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Airbag System Failure (Passenger Seat Sensor Recall)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can cause the airbag to deploy unexpectedly or not deploy at all in the event of a crash, increasing the risk of injury or death to the passenger.
symptoms: The passenger airbag warning light remains illuminated
the airbag warning light goes off intermittently
the electronic brake system activates on its own
and the vehicle is not safe to drive with a passenger in the front seat.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake booster can cause the vehicle to brake suddenly and unexpectedly, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brake booster faulty warning light illuminates on the dashboard
the brakes feel spongy or hard to engage
the vehicle may jerk or lurch when braking
and the brakes may suddenly engage without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the autonomous braking system can cause the vehicle to brake suddenly and unexpectedly, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle brakes suddenly and unexpectedly without warning
the brakes may engage without any obstacles or hazards in front of the vehicle
and the vehicle may come to a complete stop in the middle of the road.
